<div id="review_2529815806" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2529815806" />
    <a title="BookNerd" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/38511142-booknerd"><img alt="BookNerd" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1622126776p2/38511142.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2529815806?book_show_action=true">Sep 14, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="BookNerd" class="user" itemprop="url" name="BookNerd" href="/user/show/38511142-booknerd">BookNerd</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="ebook " href="/book/show/40576715-shades-of-trust">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2529815806" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7489267424695546054">I had to force myself to read book 1. I just couldn&apos;t get into it at all and it just dragged on. I hate Ethan. I decided to give book 2 a chance. Turned out it was better than book 1. The rest of the books caught my attention and I couldn&apos;t put it down. With that being said, this really shouldn&apos;t be a box set. The series is too long to read all at one time like a full novel unless it&apos;s edited down quite a bit. I think it could be done without losing the plot and storyline. I loved the characters</span>
  <span id="freeText7489267424695546054" style="display:none">I had to force myself to read book 1. I just couldn't get into it at all and it just dragged on. I hate Ethan. I decided to give book 2 a chance. Turned out it was better than book 1. The rest of the books caught my attention and I couldn't put it down. With that being said, this really shouldn't be a box set. The series is too long to read all at one time like a full novel unless it's edited down quite a bit. I think it could be done without losing the plot and storyline. I loved the characters and thought they were well-developed. As I continued to read, I begin to understand Ethan and even started to like him at the very end. I was glad to watch the evolution of the characters though the series. Gabriela was terrific. I loved how intuitive she was. The only thing that really bothered (why I really don't know) is I don't know any woman who found out what the baby's gender is at 8 weeks. Because I have read this series, I plan to go back and read Shade Of Love and Painted In Red. I think these two books will make more sense to me now.<br /><br />I voluntarily read and reviewed a free copy of this book....</span>
  <a data-text-id="7489267424695546054" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


